				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.memeorandum.com/&quot;&gt;Memeorandum&lt;/a&gt; has been a regular &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/images/2021/07/18/memeScreenShot.png&quot;&gt;stop&lt;/a&gt; for me for news for decades, is now mostly links to news that's behind paywalls. I couldn’t possibly pay for most of them, too many subs to manage, and I don’t read enough of any individual pub to justify subscribing. I do subscribe to NYT and Washington Post. But I don’t get enough value from either, honestly. This continues to be a &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/2020/08/06/133617.html?title=moneyForNews&quot;&gt;lousy situation&lt;/a&gt;. The pubs only talk about how news is broken from their point of view, but the readers point of view matters as much, if not more." created="Sun, 18 Jul 2021 20:03:25 GMT" type="outline"/>
