				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/markgraham&quot;&gt;Mark Graham&lt;/a&gt; who works at archive.org &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/MarkGraham/status/1414217978778988547&quot;&gt;reports&lt;/a&gt; that they've fixed a playback issue with &lt;a href=&quot;https://web.archive.org/web/20210702040625/http://scripting.com/&quot;&gt;their rendering&lt;/a&gt; of &quot;Scripting News&quot;. I &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/2021/07/01.html#a123740&quot;&gt;wrote&lt;/a&gt; about &lt;a href=&quot;http://scripting.com/2021/06/29.html#a131345&quot;&gt;this&lt;/a&gt; previously. That's great news. Thanks for persevering! :smile: " created="Sun, 11 Jul 2021 16:50:05 GMT" type="outline"/>
